{
  "texts": [
    "The DP framework is characterized by its concrete privacy semantics, derived from the its 'differential' interpretation.",
    "Notwithstanding, there exists a variety of DP variants, encompassing pure DP and -DP, alongside divergence-based DP definitions such as Rényi DP (Mironov, 2017) and truncated concentrated DP (Bun et al., 2018), and -DP (J.",
    "Dong et al., 2022), which are interpreted directly through a hypothesis-testing viewpoint.",
    "Among these, some DP metrics excel in terms of interpretability, while others possess more information-theoretic characteristics, making them well-suited for applications requiring tight privacy bounds, such as hyperparameter tuning (Papernot & Steinke, 2022) and information-theoretic trade-offs between privacy and utility (J.",
    "We posit that an advantageous research direction entails developing a framework for determining the most suitable privacy definition for a given task."
  ]
}